fix: Claude CLI has a 1MB buffer for MCP JSON messages. When a tool (Glob, Bash, Read) returns >1MB, the CLI crashes with 'JSON message exceeded maximum buffer size'. Previously this killed the session permanently — the session_id pointed to a dead process. Now both streaming and non-streaming paths catch ProcessError, reset session_id to None (so next call starts fresh), and return a descriptive error to the agent suggesting smaller operations. The agent can then retry with more specific queries.
